Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.51,0:03:11.75,Default,,0,0,0,,So, when did this sickness start affecting this town?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.35,0:03:14.71,Default,,0,0,0,,It's already been fourteen years...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.71,0:03:18.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone looks the same,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.20,0:03:21.11,Default,,0,0,0,,but their skin becomes frighteningly hard in places
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.11,0:03:24.22,Default,,0,0,0,,and they become unable to move their limbs.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.82,0:03:30.21,Default,,0,0,0,,By far the worst case is an old friend of mine...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.21,0:03:32.12,Default,,0,0,0,,He can't even get up anymore...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.35,0:03:35.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Where is this person?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.21,0:03:38.28,Default,,0,0,0,,He and his wife live on the western outskirts of town.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.86,0:03:46.28,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(0,1956)}All the townspeople say that their daughter is the cause of the illness.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.28,0:03:52.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Ever since that girl-Shige is her name was born...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.85,0:03:56.50,Default,,0,0,0,,the people around her came down with the sickness one after another...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.08,0:04:00.40,Default,,0,0,0,,That is a fact, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.30,0:04:04.39,Default,,0,0,0,,We've done everything we could\Nover the past fourteen years,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.39,0:04:06.52,Default,,0,0,0,,but we haven't been able to find the cause.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.52,0:04:13.31,Default,,0,0,0,,The girl hasn't spoken a word, and that has just made people more suspicious.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.70,0:04:16.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Here. This is for this month.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.64,0:04:19.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Really, what is the Master thinking...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.89,0:04:25.22,Default,,0,0,0,,If he's going to show pity on this child just because he's friends with her parents,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.22,0:04:28.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I wish he'd give us a raise instead.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.30,0:04:35.66,Default,,0,0,0,,My, that's a huge hole, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.45,0:04:38.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry, but I don't have a replacement.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.83,0:04:47.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Shige!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.85,0:04:49.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Use this.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.33,0:04:54.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Those townspeople never get tired of it, do they?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.32,0:04:58.33,Default,,0,0,0,,You should give them a piece of your mind sometimes.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.33,0:04:59.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Those are only rumors, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.44,0:05:06.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Even if they were true,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.45,0:05:10.40,Default,,0,0,0,,it wasn't your intention to make\Nyour family and friends sick, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.94,0:05:13.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Back home at my village,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.99,0:05:18.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I lost half my family and friends\N in a storm two years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.17,0:05:23.50,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why I decided to stay here\Nto earn money in place of my dad.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.54,0:05:27.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Like me, you decided this was\Nthe only way to survive, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.44,0:05:32.10,Default,,0,0,0,,I give you credit...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.69,0:05:43.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.63,0:05:43.15,Alt,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.78,0:05:46.60,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd like to ask you about that girl.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.85,0:05:51.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you another one of those doctors\N summoned by the Master?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.47,0:05:53.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know a thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.08,0:05:55.16,Default,,0,0,0,,She won't say a word to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.16,0:05:57.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Tetsu! What's keeping you?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.53,0:05:59.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay! Be right there!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.80,0:06:11.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.97,0:06:21.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Welcome home...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.27,0:06:23.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks for doing that...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.91,0:06:41.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Shige... right?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.13,0:06:45.80,Default,,0,0,0,,You can see this rust, can't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.07,0:06:48.41,Default,,0,0,0,,My name's Ginko.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.41,0:06:50.52,Default,,0,0,0,,I was only asked here to help cure the sickness.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.49,0:06:53.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not going to condemn you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.89,0:06:56.44,Default,,0,0,0,,This sickness is curable.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.21,0:06:59.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Won't you tell me about it?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.77,0:07:06.08,Default,,0,0,0,,That should be enough...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.86,0:07:10.70,Default,,0,0,0,,It's okay for you to speak in here.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.70,0:07:12.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't want to rust either, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.64,0:07:17.75,Default,,0,0,0,,You see? Nothing happens.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.70,0:07:25.25,Default,,0,0,0,,You... can see the rust, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.25,0:07:26.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.75,0:07:28.76,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}It was...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.38,0:07:33.40,Default,,0,0,0,,My voice does frightening things...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.40,0:07:36.49,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why I tried to stifle it...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.49,0:07:41.27,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}...a deep, hoarse voice that\Ndid not match her tiny body...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.65,0:07:47.42,Default,,0,0,0,,by yelling in that cave until my voice turned like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.42,0:07:51.78,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}...yet it reverberated with sweet, sober overtones...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.97,0:07:56.21,Default,,0,0,0,,But no matter how much my voice changes,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.55,0:08:01.68,Default,,0,0,0,,my voice still causes rust to appear.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.68,0:08:04.69,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}It was a voice with a mysterious sound...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.02,0:08:07.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Shige!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.72,0:08:12.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Daddy! Welcome home!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.86,0:08:16.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Hi... What's that doll?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.51,0:08:18.84,Default,,0,0,0,,It's my little sister.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.84,0:08:20.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, so that's who it is...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.29,0:08:26.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Whenever I used my voice, rust formed on the people and things around me...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.75,0:08:31.10,Default,,0,0,0,,To me, it was perfectly normal.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.10,0:08:34.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Say Shige, why don't you sing me a song?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.42,0:08:40.12,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't think it was strange, and so \NI sang songs that I liked to everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.53,0:08:45.08,Default,,0,0,0,,But they could not see it...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.70,0:08:48.31,Default,,0,0,0,,I realized it wasn't a good thing...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.31,0:08:53.59,Default,,0,0,0,,around when I turned four and \Neveryone was becoming crippled.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.17,0:08:58.10,Default,,0,0,0,,I told my father and mother about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.44,0:09:03.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Shige, you must never tell anyone about this.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.43,0:09:05.64,Default,,0,0,0,,If you do, we won't be able to live here anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.68,0:09:10.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Both of us are already unable to work.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.18,0:09:15.61,Default,,0,0,0,,We're only able to survive thanks to the kindness of the Master of the big house.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.30,0:09:18.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's live here...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.85,0:09:23.37,Default,,0,0,0,,deceiving everyone and casting \Nourselves on the Master's mercy.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.37,0:09:27.82,Default,,0,0,0,,The day will come when we can repay his kindness...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.82,0:09:31.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Until then, you mustn't use your voice... Shige.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.38,0:09:38.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Since then, I've spoken to no one.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.69,0:09:41.68,Default,,0,0,0,,It's been ten years since I've spoken to anyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.76,0:09:46.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I deserve to be despised by everyone...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.59,0:09:50.40,Default,,0,0,0,,because I chose to go on living\N with just the three of us.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.49,0:09:52.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.89,0:09:55.59,Default,,0,0,0,,The more I hear your voice, \Nthe more unusual it sounds...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.55,0:09:59.41,Default,,0,0,0,,I wonder how you're able to speak in such a voice...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.41,0:10:03.49,Default,,0,0,0,,There are levels to your voice that most people cannot even produce.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.43,0:10:09.15,Default,,0,0,0,,It may sound a bit different to you,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.15,0:10:11.92,Default,,0,0,0,,but there is a sound that sounds \Nutterly similar to your voice.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.94,0:10:14.59,Default,,0,0,0,,This isn't rust.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.63,0:10:18.26,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a mushi known as {\i1}Yasabi,{\i0} and it's alive.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.86,0:10:21.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Mushi?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.69,0:10:24.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Some can see them, others cannot.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.42,0:10:26.27,Default,,0,0,0,,They exist differently from other life.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.00,0:10:30.55,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Yasabi{\i0} are normally harmless mushi \Nthat attach themselves to
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.55,0:10:32.27,Default,,0,0,0,,dead bodies and decompose them.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.27,0:10:34.20,Default,,0,0,0,,They make a sound in the process.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.78,0:10:39.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Your voice is that sound \Nthat amplified several hundredfold.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.87,0:10:44.35,Default,,0,0,0,,So, thinking there was food, the{\i1}Yasabi{\i0} in the mountains gathered here.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.93,0:10:47.21,Default,,0,0,0,,But there was no food,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.21,0:10:50.29,Default,,0,0,0,,So they attached themselves onto even living things.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.40,0:10:53.79,Default,,0,0,0,,The answer, then, is to scatter them.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.53,0:10:56.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that possible?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.23,0:10:57.30,Default,,0,0,0,,And what's more...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.88,0:11:01.55,Default,,0,0,0,,There should be a way to return your voice to normal.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.03,0:11:16.46,Default,,0,0,0,,They're on everything...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.46,0:11:18.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't they have any preferences?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.99,0:11:29.79,Default,,0,0,0,,The entire town is evenly rust-colored...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.90,0:11:36.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.10,0:11:41.16,Default,,0,0,0,,What're you doing out here in the cold?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.16,0:11:41.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, nothing...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.53,0:11:46.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Say, aren't you afraid of Shige?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.43,0:11:49.73,Default,,0,0,0,,It's been only two years since I came to this town,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.44,0:11:54.44,Default,,0,0,0,,so I just still can't believe that\NShige is the cause of the sickness.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.93,0:11:56.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Well then...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.06,0:11:56.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.70,0:12:00.99,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Maybe that's why there's not a single Yasabi on him.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.52,0:12:06.23,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Oh, you can see the ocean from here...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.52,0:12:15.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Is it possible?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.69,0:12:27.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Just as I thought...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.99,0:12:41.03,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}If everyone's sickness is cured and I can speak again,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.82,0:12:44.03,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I can thank Tetsu-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.77,0:12:49.06,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I can tell him in my own voice.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.05,0:12:51.51,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.97,0:12:53.05,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.05,0:12:56.00,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll use your voice to chase the mushi away.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.60,0:13:01.55,Default,,0,0,0,,But, for everyone to be safe after that, you'll have to leave this town.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.19,0:13:08.43,Default,,0,0,0,,I understand. So the sickness will be cured, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.43,0:13:09.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll do anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.59,0:13:11.52,Default,,0,0,0,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.52,0:13:12.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.08,0:13:16.06,Default,,0,0,0,,There's one favor I want to ask of you...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.10,0:13:20.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I want you to teach me how to write.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.56,0:13:24.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Hi there.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.58,0:13:32.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, my towel...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.78,0:13:34.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you... Oh...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.90,0:13:35.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.61,0:13:41.55,Default,,0,0,0,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.55,0:13:43.50,Default,,0,0,0,,You found the cause?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.03,0:13:45.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Was it Shige?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.28,0:13:49.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, that was nothing but a rumor.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.16,0:13:55.60,Default,,0,0,0,,No, it might be this way...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.66,0:13:58.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Here... Let me read it for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.58,0:14:00.06,Default,,0,0,0,,G-give that back!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.58,0:14:04.57,Default,,0,0,0,,"If I speak, you will become sick, as well..."?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.57,0:14:07.57,Default,,0,0,0,,"Forgive me... And thank you..."
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.57,0:14:11.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Tetsu! Who wrote this?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.04,0:14:12.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Was it Shige?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.89,0:14:14.87,Default,,0,0,0,,No! Give it back!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.87,0:14:18.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh no, it looked like you were sympathetic to her.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.11,0:14:20.58,Default,,0,0,0,,This had to be her.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.95,0:14:22.21,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll show this to the Master.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.21,0:14:23.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't do that!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.76,0:14:26.37,Default,,0,0,0,,What're you doing, Tetsu?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.40,0:14:31.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you for everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.82,0:14:34.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, Tetsu!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.09,0:14:35.63,Default,,0,0,0,,No need to go after him.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.63,0:14:37.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Clean out the furnace right now!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.71,0:14:38.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.13,0:14:42.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Damn that Shige... She won't be \Nable to play dumb anymore!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.58,0:14:48.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Shige!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.38,0:14:52.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Run away somewhere, Shige...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.45,0:14:55.16,Default,,0,0,0,,They'll all be coming soon...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.16,0:14:57.83,Default,,0,0,0,,No telling what they'll do to you...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.11,0:15:01.77,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I can't.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.77,0:15:06.98,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Ginko-san hasn't shown me \Nhow to chase away the mushi.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.30,0:15:11.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Shige. Leave here for now.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.64,0:15:13.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait for me up there at the ridge.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.31,0:15:18.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll show you how to chase away the mushi\N after I've convinced everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.86,0:15:20.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll go with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.28,0:15:23.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't stay in this town anymore...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.00,0:15:26.32,Default,,0,0,0,,That ridge is in the direction of my home village.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.32,0:15:27.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Also it's dangerous to go alo...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.20,0:15:28.47,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm counting on you.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.85,0:15:31.57,Default,,0,0,0,,You can do it, can't you, Shige?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.83,0:15:45.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Ginko-san, why are you protecting Shige?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.61,0:15:46.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Bring Shige out here!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.95,0:15:48.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Make her apologize.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.22,0:15:52.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Banishing Shige won't cure the sickness.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.59,0:15:54.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Besides, it's not Shige's fault.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.64,0:16:01.14,Default,,0,0,0,,All Shige did was talk, laugh and\N sing like any other child.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.53,0:16:06.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Her voice had an element in it that attracted the cause of the sickness... that's all.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.06,0:16:09.33,Default,,0,0,0,,We don't give a damn about that!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.33,0:16:13.16,Default,,0,0,0,,What we want to know is how she plans to apologize to those she made sick.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.86,0:16:15.33,Default,,0,0,0,,If it's an apology you want,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.33,0:16:18.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Shige has been doing that for ten years.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.65,0:16:21.71,Default,,0,0,0,,If she had broken her vow and given an excuse,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.71,0:16:24.31,Default,,0,0,0,,she could've managed to stop fanning your suspicions.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.95,0:16:28.17,Default,,0,0,0,,She bore her sin the entire time.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.85,0:16:31.10,Default,,0,0,0,,That doesn't mean we can forgive her!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.10,0:16:34.82,Default,,0,0,0,,My child is her age, but she can't even walk!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.82,0:16:35.68,Default,,0,0,0,,My child, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.30,0:16:38.68,Default,,0,0,0,,She will, of course, make amends.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.27,0:16:43.69,Default,,0,0,0,,If it was Shige's voice that brought the sickness here, it is her voice that can make it go away.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.94,0:16:48.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Couldn't you call it even then?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.22,0:16:52.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone who had something to do with this sickness suffered the same way.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.69,0:17:04.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Shige, about that letter...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.27,0:17:08.63,Default,,0,0,0,,It sounded as though you were going to leave town...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.61,0:17:12.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you going to do that after the sickness is cured?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.18,0:17:15.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you have somewhere to go?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.09,0:17:20.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, would you come to my village as well?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.54,0:17:24.74,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a fishing village that had most of the homes and boats washed away...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.74,0:17:26.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone is working together \Nto rebuild it little by little.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.82,0:17:29.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Things will somehow work out. \NWhy don't you do that?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.12,0:17:40.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Shige!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.36,0:17:57.41,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}They're not here... Did something happen?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.59,0:18:16.49,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I have to call for help...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.53,0:18:19.07,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}My voice...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.39,0:18:24.29,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}If I call at this distance...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.19,0:18:27.16,Default,,0,0,0,,This sickness is curable.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.63,0:18:31.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Shige!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.17,0:18:33.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Tetsu!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.58,0:18:50.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}That unmistakable voice was echoing\N through the mountains.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.66,0:18:54.99,Alt,,0,0,0,,{\an8}Help!!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.42,0:19:09.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Hm? My legs feel lighter...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.62,0:19:11.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Hm? So do mine...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.29,0:19:25.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Shige! Are you okay? How about Tetsu?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.42,0:19:31.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry... I'm so sorry...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.11,0:19:34.27,Default,,0,0,0,,I made you get the sickness, too, Tetsu-san...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.83,0:19:42.28,Default,,0,0,0,,He's just unconscious.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.84,0:19:44.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Relax.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.34,0:19:46.16,Default,,0,0,0,,He won't get the sickness.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.78,0:19:55.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Shige!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.28,0:19:59.80,Default,,0,0,0,,You're all right! Look... my legs are...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.79,0:20:08.81,Default,,0,0,0,,As it turned out, you did something \Nvery close to what I had in mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.13,0:20:13.99,Default,,0,0,0,,My plan was to have your voice echo through the mountains that surround this town,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.99,0:20:17.16,Default,,0,0,0,,to disperse the {\i1}Yasabi{\i0} gathered \Nin the town into the mountains.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.82,0:20:24.85,Default,,0,0,0,,But the location had to be that ridge\Nwith the ocean behind it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.85,0:20:27.83,Default,,0,0,0,,That's because Yasabi dislike sea breezes.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.65,0:20:35.83,Default,,0,0,0,,The rust at the edge of town where sea breezes blow in was ordinary rust.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.99,0:20:40.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Tetsu never got the sickness because he was raised in a fishing village
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.87,0:20:44.61,Default,,0,0,0,,and often stood out in the sea breeze even after coming to this town.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.39,0:20:49.85,Default,,0,0,0,,If you live near the sea, \Nyou can live a normal life, as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.23,0:20:53.73,Default,,0,0,0,,But you've scattered only a small fraction of the mushi.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.93,0:20:56.84,Default,,0,0,0,,You'll have to repeat what you did for years
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.84,0:20:58.91,Default,,0,0,0,,or you'll never get rid of them all.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.91,0:21:03.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Your voice might be first to give out.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.51,0:21:10.74,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(0,1330)}I don't mind at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.74,0:21:14.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I vaguely remember—
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.02,0:21:18.35,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(0,1680)}the village before there wasn't much rust.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.49,0:21:22.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Back then, I really loved this town.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.82,0:21:29.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to do anything I can to bring\N it back to the way it was before...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.37,0:21:34.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Later, after the girl left the town,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.40,0:21:37.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}They say the sickness gradually went away.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.58,0:21:39.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Shige!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.11,0:21:41.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Headed to the ridge?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.22,0:21:42.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.35,0:21:43.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll go with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.86,0:21:47.52,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The townspeople say they still sometimes hear,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.41,0:21:51.07,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}though just faintly, a very hoarse,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.77,0:21:56.35,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}but strangely lovely and familiar singing voice
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.02,0:22:02.73,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(0,3800)}{\i1}echoing through the mountains.
